“Rock paper scissors” (pronounced and sometimes spelled “rock, paper, scissors”) is a hand game usually played between two people, in which each player simultaneously forms one of three shapes with an outstretched hand. These shapes are “rock” (a simple fist), “paper” (a flat hand), and “scissors” (a fist with the index and middle fingers together forming a V). The game has only three possible outcomes other than a tie: a player who decides to play rock will beat another player who has chosen scissors (“rock crushes scissors”) but will lose to one who has played paper (“paper covers rock”); a play of paper will lose to a play of scissors (“scissors cut paper”). If both players choose the same shape, the game is tie

In computer terms, a key is a value that is used to group together data that are associated with that value.

Descent is that part of a kinship system that identifies a person’s genealogical affiliation: i.e., descent group or line, or who you are descended from. The system upon which a kinship group is established depends on the society in which it is found. There are a number of different systems but all systems will trace relations of some form through either the mother’s or father’s line.
UNILINEAL : A unilineal descent system is one in which the kids of one sex are thought of as related to their father exclusively (and not to their mother) or their mother exclusively (and not to their father). Most unilineal systems have a joint house in which the descent group live and share property ownership. This means that only a man’s son’s or a woman’s daughter’s maintain the firm ties to the family. One half of the family is linked to the father and one half to the mother, but the family as a whole has only one last name.
MATRILINEAL : A matrilineal descent system is one in which a person can trace his or her “blood” descent through the mother. It is the blood ties a person has with his or her maternal kin. Therefore a male matrilineal heir inherits from his uncle, who is his mother’s brother, rather than from his father. This system forms the basis of a matrilineal clan, which is a social group formed by tracing the descent of maternal kin. There are some matrilineal societies supported by strong social ties between a female and her brother, as opposed to her husband. This is a very narrow passage between the mainland and the northern cape of Vynora. Due to the narrowness, it is named the Strait of Shedetang rather than Shedetang Bay, despite the bay being nonexistent to the north. You must either sail safely through this passage or detour around the north. Although the detour adds an extra day, the detouring route is often preferred by larger merchant ships. A large ship must always be wary of pirates and unfavorable winds and currents while in such confined routes. Though it is a pain to dock safely in the region, the chance for loot (and furs) can be very enticing to a pirate. With a swift force, one will rip a hole through the hull, and capsize, crumble, or destroy the ship. As with many straits, the southern current is the best way to travel through Shedetang Strait. Though don't let that fool you. There are currents causing waves that crash up over 40 feet along its shores.

Klonki, who has a minor bonus for using zinc, and a slightly enhanced chance at rarity, should endeavor to use the highest quality, and rarest material available, such as huge chunks of zinc, and bloom.
